  "description": "CONGESTED-link teleoperation 5G latency: the SAME real N-HiTS geforce traffic (cloud-gaming uplink for control, downlink video for camera) as 5g_nhits_geforce, but mapped through a DEGRADED link -- reduced cell capacity (higher load -> larger queueing delay), a longer base RTT, and a timeline dominated by the 'poor' congestion regime with periodic handover outages. Models the same remote-driving app on a loaded/edge cell rather than a clean dedicated link. Pairs with 5g_nhits_geforce (good link) as the harder of a two-condition link-quality study. Calibrated one-way (verified via simulation/latency_profile.py): command p50 148 / p95 320 / p99 700 ms; camera p50 348 / p95 675 / p99 800 / spikes to 1100 ms. ~5x the good-link command delay, ~3.5x the camera delay. Drivable but demanding; brief (0.4-0.6 s) handover outages, no multi-second blackout.",
